                            <comment id="15136952" author="ashish singhi" created="Mon, 8 Feb 2016 13:43:13 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;As per the current design the replication of WAL data starts from the beginning of the current WAL file. So in this case the table &apos;t1&apos; entries already present in the current WAL will get replicated to peer &apos;p2&apos;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Didn&apos;t find any way to set the current WAL writer offset while adding the peer in RS. &lt;br/&gt;
One work around we think is to roll the WAL while adding the peer in each RS. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Any other suggestions ? &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
